[[Category:Solar power]]

The '''''Tasman Spirit''''' is a Greek registered [[oil tanker]].  The tanker was launched in February 1979 and was formerly called the ''Mabini'' and ''Kenko''.

On July 28, 2003 she ran aground near the city of [[Karachi]]. Over 33,000 tons of oil spilled into the [[Arabian Sea]] in what is considered by some to be the largest environmental disaster in [[Pakistan]]'s history. According to the [[IUCN]] 16 kilometres of coastline has been polluted.

The ship's insurer offered 10 million rupees (about $180,000 [[US dollar]]s in 2003) in compensation to the Karachi port authorities, and agreed to pay all cleaning expenses.

